// ch05 §5.12: a by-reference-capturing closure is a lifetime-tracked
// value subject to the same alias-XOR-mutability rule as any other
// reference ([§5.2](ch05-static-checks.md)) -- a second mutable
// reference to the same local, taken and used while the closure is still
// alive (not yet called), conflicts with the closure's own live borrow.
// Mirrors `two_mutable_borrows_conflict_is_rejected` in
// 04_references_borrow, but one side is a closure instead of a plain
// `T&` local.
int main() {
    int x = 5;
    auto f = [&x]() { return x; };
    int& r = x;
    r = 10;
    return f();
}
